OL,3,CVictims' families come together to
OL,4,Cdemand stronger rights
OL,6,F"I cannot fathom how it could even be
OL,7,Fconceived that it's appropriate to say
OL,8,Fvictims have the right to request, but
OL,9,Fwe have no statutory rights to know
OL,10,Fanything.
OL,12,F"If a crime is committed, whether it's
OL,13,Fa mental health related crime or not,
OL,14,Fthere is a perpetrator, there are
OL,15,Fvictims and that's fact. The whole
OL,16,Fsystem has to be respectful of both
OL,17,Fsides and the rights of both sides,
OL,18,Fand this clearly isn't doing that."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/14
