OL,3,CVictims' families come together to
OL,4,Cdemand stronger rights
OL,6,FVicki added: "We've been let down at
OL,7,Fevery hurdle by every agency. The
OL,8,Fsystem has already failed us, and
OL,9,Fthey're asking us to put our trust in
OL,10,Fthem again. My trust for the entire
OL,11,Fsystem has just gone out of the
OL,12,Fwindow."
OL,14,FTheir concerns are being echoed by the
OL,15,Fcharity Hundred Families, who support
OL,16,Fpeople affected by mental health
OL,17,Frelated killings. Around 100 people a
OL,18,Fyear are killed by seriously mentally
OL,19,Fill offenders.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/14
