OL,3,CVictims' families come together to
OL,4,Cdemand stronger rights
OL,6,FFounder Julian Hendy said: "As the
OL,7,Fbill stands, victims will have no
OL,8,Fstatutory right to be told about
OL,9,Fdecisions affecting the detention,
OL,10,Fleave, or discharge of mentally
OL,11,Fdisordered offenders unless the
OL,12,Fauthorities 'consider it appropriate'.
OL,14,F"There is no obligation even to
OL,15,Fconsult victims, no duty to explain
OL,16,Fdecisions, and no right to challenge
OL,17,For appeal if information is withheld.
OL,18,FFor bereaved families, this is not
OL,19,Fjust a loophole. It's a kick in the
OL,20,Fteeth for victims."
